   {:e #blake3 "51b7173280e39fcf3e7ea14c035c024dc0ac1cdf8c0762e72d4c6fa2d3674fd1" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: The definitive test of braid's core hypothesis: does the system learn across sessions?\n\nPROTOCOL:\nSession 1 (Agent 1 — cold start):\n- Fresh braid init on Go CLI (no concepts)\n- 10 observations exploring freely, no guidance\n- Harvest -> concepts crystallize\n- Record: packages covered, surprise per observation, concepts formed\n\nSession 2 (Agent 2 — seeded):\n- New agent. braid seed from Session 1's harvest\n- 10 observations, following emergent concept structure + frontier recs\n- Harvest -> concepts refine\n- Record: same metrics. Compare to Session 1.\n\nSession 3 (Agent 3 — twice-seeded):\n- New agent. braid seed from Session 2's harvest\n- 10 observations, following refined concepts + discrepancy steering\n- Record: same metrics. Compare to Sessions 1 and 2.\n\nCONVERGENCE METRICS:\n(A) Surprise trajectory: mean surprise per session should DECREASE (Agent 3 < Agent 2 < Agent 1 for familiar territory).\n(B) Coverage rate: unique packages observed / total observations should INCREASE (guidance directs to unexplored areas).\n(C) Silence ratio: fraction of observations with one-line confirms should INCREASE (model matches reality).\n(D) Qualitative: does Agent 3 report 'the seed helped me skip rediscovery'?\n\nSCORING:\n- Converging on all 4 metrics = PASS. Braid learns.\n- Flat = harvest/seed broken.\n- Diverging = system harmful.\n\nThe subagent prompts must be IDENTICAL across all 3 sessions except for the seed. This controls for agent variability.\n\nDEPENDS-ON: INQ-TEST (all tests must pass first).\n\nACCEPTANCE: (A) 3 sessions executed sequentially with harvest/seed between. (B) All 4 convergence metrics computed. (C) Results recorded as braid observations. (D) Verdict: converging/flat/diverging." :op :assert}
